{"article_id":"RO8KXAQM9mKQ7KBC","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Back from its one-week July 4 recess , the Senate is zeroing in on student loans Wednesday ,","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"poised to take up bills","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"addressing the interest rates on subsidized federal loans","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"after a key rate doubled last week .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"After Congress refused to act last month ,","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"the rate","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"borrowers pay on subsidized Stafford loans","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"- which make up about 40 percent of federal education loans -","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"doubled from 3.4 percent to 6.8 percent on July 1 .","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"Pressure is now mounting on Congress","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"to come up with a fix","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"before many student loans are issued later this summer ,","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"but the various sides appear unable to come together","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"- even though they ' re not too far apart on what they seem to want .","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"Even the measure","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"passed by House Republicans in May ,","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"which is criticized by most Democrats ,","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"isn ' t too far from the plan in President Obama ' s budget proposal .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"Both call for a long-term fix","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"that would peg the interest rate to US Treasury borrowing rates .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"Within Senate Democratic ranks , meanwhile , there is a strong split","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"- epitomized Tuesday by dueling news conferences","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"held by different factions of the party after a closed-door lunch .","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"Some Senate Democrats ,","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"including Joe Manchin of West Virginia and Thomas Carper of Delaware , along with Angus King of Maine , an Independent","depth":13},{"id":25,"text":"who caucuses with the Democrats ,","depth":13},{"id":26,"text":"touted the bipartisan solution","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"they ' ve been pushing ,","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"which differs from the House Republican plan","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"but which also would peg interest rates to the 10-year Treasury rate .","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"But Senate majority leader Harry Reid and other top Democrats criticized that solution as well as the one from House Republicans .","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"\" Speaker Boehner says","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"the House has acted","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"and the ball is in the Senate ' s court .","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"But Democrats can ' t support a plan","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"that would be worse for students","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"than doing nothing at all , \"","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"Senator Reid said in remarks on the Senate floor on Tuesday .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"Reid and many other Senate Democrats favor once again passing a short-term fix","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"- extending the 3.4 percent rate one more year ,","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"which they would pay for","depth":13},{"id":41,"text":"by changing some tax rules on certain retirement accounts .","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"They say","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"such a short-term solution would enable them to focus on deeper , more systemic problems and long-term solutions to college affordability in the fall ,","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"when they take up the Higher Education Act .","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"Others see it as Congress once again punting a thorny issue down the road","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"rather than addressing it .","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"\" Why should we have a political one-year fix for 2 million students","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"and leave 9 million more paying rates","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"that are higher","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"than they should ,","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"7 million of them middle-income students ? \"","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"asked Sen. Lamar Alexander","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"( R )","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"of Tennessee ,","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"speaking to reporters after the lunch Tuesday .","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"He was referring to the fact","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"that the one-year extension would apply only to subsidized loans ,","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"while the bipartisan solution","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"he supports","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"would also lower interest rates , at least in the short term , for students","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"getting unsubsidized federal loans as well .","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"Some college finance experts say","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"a short-term solution is unlikely to really encourage Congress to address bigger issues in the fall .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"\" If they push this off to the Higher Education Act reauthorization ,","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"then this issue will again dominate the conversation ,","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"and there are many other issues","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"lawmakers need to tackle , \"","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"says Jason Delisle , director of the Federal Education Budget Project for the New America Foundation ,","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"who hopes","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"Congress will come up with a long-term solution for government-issued education loans .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"\" We ' re not going to come up with anything different in the next year .","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"We know what ' s out there , \"","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"he says .","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"If it gets put off another year ,","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"Mr. Delisle adds ,","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"\" we ' re going to spend another year debating the exact same options on the table \"","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"that are there now . -","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"The proposal already passed by House Republicans ,","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"which would tie interest rates to the 10-year US Treasury borrowing rate plus 2.5 percent for all Stafford loans and 4.5 percent for all PLUS loans .","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"Rates would vary with the market ,","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"but Stafford interest rates would be capped at 8.5 percent ,","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"and PLUS loan rates would be capped at 10.5 percent .","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"- The bipartisan Senate proposal ,","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"which would peg loan rates to the 10-year Treasury rate plus 1.85 percent for Stafford undergraduate loans , 3.4 percent for Stafford graduate loans , and 4.4 percent for PLUS loans .","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"The rates would be locked in for the life of the loan .","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"While there would be no cap ,","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"the consolidation rate for loans would be 8.25 percent .","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"- The proposal","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"favored by Reid , Sen. Tom Harkin of Iowa , and most other prominent Senate Democrats ,","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"which would extend the current","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"( until it expired )","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"3.4 percent rate on subsidized Stafford loans one more year ,","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"and would not change the interest rates for unsubsidized Stafford loans or PLUS loans .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"Reid , Senator Harkin , and other Democrats have criticized both plans","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"to peg the rates to treasuries ,","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"saying","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"they would rather see the current rates double","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"than endorse a solution","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"they suspect","depth":14},{"id":100,"text":"will be worse for students in the long term ,","depth":14},{"id":101,"text":"and they seem unlikely to budge .","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"They ' ve criticized the bipartisan plan","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"for not having caps ,","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"and they say","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"it could leave future students vulnerable to high rates","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"if borrowing rates go up significantly .","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"But talk of no caps on interest rates ,","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"says Delisle of New America ,","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"is somewhat disingenuous","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"given that students will still be able to consolidate loans at 8.25 percent","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"- one way","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"to bring loans down -","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"and will also have the option","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"to cap payments on the basis of income .","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"\" Which would you rather have , an interest rate cap or a payment cap ? \"","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"Delisle asks .","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"\" The payment cap is better ,","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"and that already exists . \"","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"Meanwhile , despite the heated debate and party schisms","depth":5},{"id":120,"text":"that the student loan interest rate is causing ,","depth":5},{"id":121,"text":"higher education experts note","depth":5},{"id":122,"text":"that it ' s really a side show to the bigger issues","depth":6},{"id":123,"text":"contributing to college affordability problems","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"-","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"most of which get little attention .","depth":7},{"id":126,"text":"\" We ' re letting the students take a bigger and bigger piece of [ college costs ] ,","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"and are allowing states to disproportionately cut higher education ,","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"and we ' re floundering around ,","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"looking desperately at small answers to big problems , \"","depth":7},{"id":130,"text":"says Pat Callan , president of the Higher Education Policy Institute in San Jose , Calif .","depth":5},{"id":131,"text":"Mr. Callan isn ' t optimistic","depth":6},{"id":132,"text":"that Congress will be able to address those issues on its own ,","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"even if it tries ,","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"noting","depth":6},{"id":135,"text":"that it will take some combination of the federal government","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"working with states","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"to find answers .","depth":7},{"id":138,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":6},{"id":139,"text":"you care about","depth":6},{"id":140,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":5},{"id":141,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":5},{"id":142,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":5},{"id":143,"text":"\" The ideas are so small ,","depth":7},{"id":144,"text":"and the magnitude of the problem is so huge","depth":8},{"id":145,"text":"that it really threatens American competitiveness of the workforce and the opportunities of the next generation ,","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"but I don ' t see any willingness","depth":7},{"id":147,"text":"to have the bigger discussion , \"","depth":7},{"id":148,"text":"says Callan .","depth":5},{"id":149,"text":"\" So yes , we should put a band-aid on [ student loan interest rates going up ] ,","depth":6},{"id":150,"text":"and yes , it ' s important .","depth":6},{"id":151,"text":"But","depth":6},{"id":152,"text":"if we think","depth":8},{"id":153,"text":"we ' ve solved any serious long-term problem about the financing of higher education in this country","depth":9},{"id":154,"text":"once we ' ve done","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"that is to be pretty deluded . \"","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":311,"left":274,"right":310,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":274,"left":164,"right":273,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":159,"right":163,"relation":"conte